#Localization

---

Localization is used to render the proper string translations in markup, notifications, and for exception handling.
The localization translation key/value pairs must be initialized during application startup, typically in the run portion
of the main module.

##Enabling Localization

 - Include the proper top-level, application, module dependency.  In most cases, common.exceptionHandler will provide
 an all encompassing dependency for the localization and notification modules.

 In most cases, common.exceptionHandler will provide an all encompassing dependency for the localization and notification modules.

        angular.module('ccApp', [
                ...
                'common.exceptionHandler'

## Intialization

To initialize and retrieve the localization key value pairs from a module:

      .run(function (i18nMessages) {
            i18nMessages.init('locales', 'en');
        });

## Filters (as used in expressions to affect markup)

    {{ 'first.and.last' | i18n:{ firstName: 'foo', lastName: 'bar'} }}

See <a href="index.html#/api/common.filters:i18n">common.filters:i18n</a>

## JavaScript

For a message key equal to:

    first.and.last: 'My first name is {(firstName}} and my last is {{lastName}}.'

In JavaScript:

    localizationMessages.get('first.and.last', {
                 firstName: 'foo',
                 lastName: 'bar'
             });

See <a href="index.html#/api/common.localizedMessages:localizedMessages">common.localizedMessages:localizedMessages</a>

